name: TeeTotal Fox
description:
The TeeTotal Fox was born when we teamed up with our friends at Jthree Concepts to find that little something that represents what we stand for. Our vision to blur the lines between wearing a t shirt and a piece of art, only ever selling t shirts in limited runs, and all that stuff we go on about in the ‘About Us’ section… well that’s all summed up in this little fox. 

Jthree Concepts is Seattle-based artist Jared K. Nickerson. Jared is a professional digital illustrator, originally from Halifax, Nova Scotia. With various moves westward across North America he is now based in Seattle, WA. Jared is co-founder of renowned vector community Blood Sweat Vector (BSV). 
His main focus is character, logo, videogame, editorial, and textile design.  He also specializes in art direction, branding, and consulting. His client list includes Nike, Adidas, Coca-Cola, Activision, K2 Snowboards, and CultureClub to name a few.  

As well as being an illustrator, Jared is also an amateur music producer, song writer, and vocalist. His band, Dead Astronauts, just released their first single, "Favorite Lover", which is available on Amazon, Beatport, & iTunes.

name: Helium Works
description:
There’s hitting the jackpot and then there’s finding Athur Sinai’s work in a small corner of the internet. We had the idea for a typography based design and immediately fell in love with this artist. Athur is a passionate designer encompassing all the values of TeeTotal Clothing. He believes that design can touch people’s hearts, and this passion and enthusiasm gave us no choice but to get him on board with our project.  

Athur Sinai is an Indonesian Graphic Designer, specialising in branding, pattern and ornate designs. 
He was born in 1989 and started work as a freelance designer and illustrator in 2010, where he currently lives in Bali, Indonesia. 

The Helium Works design was inspired by various kinds of ornamental carving seen by Athur whilst growing up in Indonesia. Using pattern and ornament designs, multiple objects have been combined into a single complex unit creating the beautiful typography letters ‘TT’.

name: Happy Dog
description:
We scoured the globe for the perfect picture of a Dog rocking Smart Casual. During the search we discovered Libby Watkins with her quirky pencil drawings and we instantly fell for her. She’s another artist we know you will love and we expect big things in the future. 

Libby Watkins is a fine artist/ illustrator/ designer currently based in Sydney, Australia. Specialising mainly in tonal pencil drawings with just a splash of colour, she approaches realism with a refreshing infusion of character.

name: Chasca
description:
We stumbled across Dooom’s art on the streets of Bristol in a little boutique and immediately fell in love with his style and mysterious pseudonym.  To this day we don’t know his real name but we’re thankful he replied to our emails.

We asked him for a small bio on himself and he politely replied 'DOOOM is a UK based Graphic Designer'

The mystery lives on..

name: The Dachshund Red
description:
Well where to start with Sophie? we've been working together since the very start of TeeTotal Clothing and had lots of fun along the way. We hope that we can be a stepping stone to the bright future ahead of her.

Sophie Wilson is currently studying in the third year of a BA (Hons) Graphic Design degree at Leeds College of Art. With a background in illustrative and typographic design, she plans to spend this year expanding upon both her personal and professional design portfolio by specialising in branding having gained insight into the subject whislt on two placements in the summer months of 2012.

After graduating next summer, she plans to work in a small branding studio (potentially in Leeds or Newcastle) finding herself the dream studio apartment and fulfilling a life-long ambition of getting a pet tortoise (name Winston). Look out for Sophie (and Winston) in the future.

Portfolio of work:
www.sophiewilsondesign.com
